description:
was here for dinner on Tues with Wifey, Mom, and little Sis.  always wanted to come here - it's such an impressive-looking space from the outside.  

pretty solid restaurant.  been to their sister restaurant (Salt House) which is pretty good too.  food's prepared well, good service and nice inside (though not elegant - but it's called town hall!).  they have an upstairs room that sits 40; this would be good for a b-day party.  ambiance is OK.  it's noisy, and probably too many suits as folks will do deals and have work dinners here.  but it's pleasant enough i suppose.

-APPETIZERS: tuna tartare, mussels and italian sausage, and ham / cheese toast;

-ENTREES: rainbow trout and alaskan halibut;

-DESSERT: butterscotch and chocolate pot de creme and really rich hot chocolate.

prices are decent enough.  you'll prob spend about 50-60 / person.  had a few glasses of wine too.  worth a visit.  good place to meet with friends after work.
